<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="440" pageId="0" pageNumber="439" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1944,2036]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,152,625]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="440" pageId="0" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1978,2002]" pageId="0" pageNumber="439">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from other related fulviine genera by the following characters: rather ovoid body shape; brown-castaneous basic coloration; uniformly distributed, short, silvery, scalelike setae covering body surface, that are broadened toward apex (
<figureCitation box="[418,483,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1989,2011]" captionTargetBox="[168,1435,679,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,679,1963]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Euchilofulvius yangon, holotype female. A &amp; B. Dorsal habitus in live. C. Dry preserved specimen in left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
Fig. 
<number box="[469,483,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolski" box="[498,782,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" refString="Wolski, A. &amp; Gorczyca, J. (2014) Notes on the genera Peritropisca Carvalho &amp; Lorenzato and Rewafulvius Carvalho (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Cylapinae), with the description of a new species of Peritropisca from Indonesia. Zootaxa, 3753 (2), 155 - 166. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3753.2.5" type="journal article" year="2014">
Wolski &amp; Gorczyca, 
<number box="[726,782,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 
<number box="[849,876,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="25.0">25</number>
–26, 29, 
<number box="[972,1002,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="32.0">32</number>
); generally matte or shagreened dorsum and thoracic pleura (Wolski &amp; Gorczyca, 
<number box="[631,687,186,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="2015.0">2015</number>
, fig. 29, 32); vertex with T-shaped shallow groove, composed of longitudinal, medial groove and transverse concaved region situated near posterior margin of vertex (
<bibRefCitation author="Wolski" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" refString="Wolski, A. &amp; Gorczyca, J. (2014) Notes on the genera Peritropisca Carvalho &amp; Lorenzato and Rewafulvius Carvalho (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Cylapinae), with the description of a new species of Peritropisca from Indonesia. Zootaxa, 3753 (2), 155 - 166. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3753.2.5" type="journal article" year="2014">
Wolski &amp; Gorczyca, 
<number box="[270,326,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="2014.0">2014</number>
, figs. 
<number box="[398,469,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="25.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="25.0">25–26</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); short, filiform antennal segments III and IV; labial segment I short, weakly reaching beyond middle of gula (
<figureCitation box="[418,481,290,313]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1989,2011]" captionTargetBox="[168,1435,679,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,679,1963]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Euchilofulvius yangon, holotype female. A &amp; B. Dorsal habitus in live. C. Dry preserved specimen in left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
Fig. 
<number box="[471,481,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C); hemelytron strongly narrowed basally with distinct tubercles at constricted portion (
<bibRefCitation author="Wolski" box="[158,538,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" refString="Wolski, A. &amp; Gorczyca, J. (2014) Notes on the genera Peritropisca Carvalho &amp; Lorenzato and Rewafulvius Carvalho (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Cylapinae), with the description of a new species of Peritropisca from Indonesia. Zootaxa, 3753 (2), 155 - 166. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3753.2.5" type="journal article" year="2014">
Wolski &amp; Gorczyca, 
<number box="[393,449,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="2014.0">2014</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[508,538,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="29.0">29</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); scent gland efferent system absent (
<bibRefCitation author="Wolski" box="[955,1335,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" refString="Wolski, A. &amp; Gorczyca, J. (2014) Notes on the genera Peritropisca Carvalho &amp; Lorenzato and Rewafulvius Carvalho (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Cylapinae), with the description of a new species of Peritropisca from Indonesia. Zootaxa, 3753 (2), 155 - 166. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3753.2.5" type="journal article" year="2014">
Wolski &amp; Gorczyca, 
<number box="[1190,1246,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="2014.0">2014</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[1305,1335,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="32.0">32</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Further diagnostic characters are provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorczyca" box="[555,738,360,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" refString="Gorczyca, J. (1999) On the Euchilofulvius - complex (Heteroptera: Miridae: Cylapinae). Genus, 12, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1999">
Gorczyca (
<number box="[672,730,360,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="440" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,152,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,394,418]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[335,489,394,417]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Euchilofulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[335,489,394,417]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Euchilofulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily recognized by the above characters, particularly the silvery, scalelike setae, each of which has the flattened, apically widened shape, T-shaped shallow groove on the vertex, short labial segment I, basally constricted hemelytron with a row of distinct tubercles, and greatly reduced scent efferent system (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1408,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1989,2011]" captionTargetBox="[168,1435,679,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,679,1963]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Euchilofulvius yangon, holotype female. A &amp; B. Dorsal habitus in live. C. Dry preserved specimen in left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
Fig. 
<number box="[1397,1408,464,487]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolski" box="[151,450,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" refString="Wolski, A. &amp; Gorczyca, J. (2014) Notes on the genera Peritropisca Carvalho &amp; Lorenzato and Rewafulvius Carvalho (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Cylapinae), with the description of a new species of Peritropisca from Indonesia. Zootaxa, 3753 (2), 155 - 166. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3753.2.5" type="journal article" year="2014">Wolski &amp; Gorczyca, 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 25–26, 29, 
<number box="[600,630,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="32.0">32</number>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorczyca" box="[656,843,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" refString="Gorczyca, J. (1999) On the Euchilofulvius - complex (Heteroptera: Miridae: Cylapinae). Genus, 12, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1999">
Gorczyca (
<number box="[779,835,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested two subgenera, 
<taxonomicName box="[1155,1309,498,521]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Euchilofulvius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1155,1309,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Euchilofulvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1322,1385,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,296,533,556]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Lepidofulvius</emphasis>
Poppius. Based on his classification system, the below-described new species may belong to the latter subgenus. However, we do not use subgeneric level taxa in this work, because two subgenera are currently separated from each other only by the structure of the antennal segment II.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
